[
    {
        "content": "<p>I am implementing tactics using macros. After a macro that expands to a \"cases $name\" the user sees two goals. However What You See is NOT What You Get: the internal goal name is really  \"<a href=\"mailto:a.mp.inl._@.VerboseMatita.Basic._hyg.4370\">a.mp.inl._@.VerboseMatita.Basic._hyg.4370</a>\", but what is printed is just \"a.mp.inl\".</p>\n<p>The consequence is that users may try to use the  \"case inl\" tactic that would work if inl was a real suffix, but it is not.</p>\n<p>Am I doing something wrong? Is there a way to (re)name the goals to avoid the _@.XXX suffix? <br>\nOr is it a Lean bug I should report? Maybe suffix computation should ignore every \"_@.XXX\" suffix?</p>",
        "id": 454274169,
        "sender_full_name": "Claudio Sacerdoti Coen",
        "timestamp": 1721992127
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That's weird, <code>case</code> does erase macro scopes. Do you have an MWE?</p>",
        "id": 454274626,
        "sender_full_name": "Sebastian Ullrich",
        "timestamp": 1721992314
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I have a smallish example. Trying to minimize this one in several ways make the issue disappear.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">axiom</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">axiom</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mem</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">infix</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">50</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">priority</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">high</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\" ∈ \"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mem</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">axiom</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ax_extensionality</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"n\">Z</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Z</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Z</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"n\">A</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">axiom</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">union</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">set</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">infix</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">70</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">priority</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">high</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\" ∪ \"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">union</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">axiom</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">K1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">axiom</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">K2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">axiom</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ax_union1</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"n\">Z</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Z</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∪</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">B</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">K1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">K2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">union_symmetric</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"bp\">∪</span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"bp\">∪</span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">intros</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ax_extensionality</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Z</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">U</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">H</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">K1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">K2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ax_union1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Z</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">U</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">H</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">case</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">inl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">--- error here: inl is not a suffix because the goal name is really a.inl._@.VerboseMatita.Bug._hyg.1269</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
